HEADWORD: Trapes
<hw>Trapes</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Trape</er>.]</ety> <def>A slattern; an idle, sluttish, or untidy
woman.</def> <mark>[Obs. or Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trapes</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Trapes
<hw>Trapes</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To go about in an idle or
slatternly fashion; to trape; to traipse.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>
<rj><au>Thackeray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trapezate</ent>⟦br⟧
